PVC ceiling panels are lightweight interior ceiling systems made from polyvinyl chloride, designed as a practical, low-maintenance alternative to traditional plaster or gypsum ceilings. They are especially popular in residential and commercial spaces because they are water-resistant, termite-proof, and unaffected by humidity, making them well suited for bathrooms, kitchens, laundry areas, and tropical climates. PVC ceiling panels are typically manufactured in modular planks or sheets that interlock for quick and clean installation, often installed on metal or timber framing. Their smooth surface is easy to clean, does not require repainting, and is resistant to mold and staining, which reduces long-term maintenance costs. Aesthetically, PVC ceiling panels are available in a wide range of colors, finishes, and patterns, including wood-grain and minimalist designs, allowing them to fit both modern and functional interiors. While they do not offer the same acoustic performance or premium feel as some other ceiling materials, their affordability, durability, and moisture resistance make PVC ceiling panels a highly practical solution for efficient and hygienic interior ceiling applications.